{#-
  DescriptionList — semantic <dl><dt><dd> list of term/definition pairs.

  Pure-semantic primitive — 0 controller, 0 JS. Two layouts:
   - stacked (default) : <dt> above <dd>, vertical pairs, gap between pairs.
   - side-by-side      : <dt> | <dd> on a single grid row, terms aligned in
                          the inline-start column.

  Parameters:
    items     (array,  required) [{ term: string, definition: string }, ...].
                                  Each entry's `term` and `definition` are
                                  pre-resolved strings (consumer calls |trans).
    layout    (string, optional) stacked (default) | side-by-side
    className (string, optional) extra utility classes on the wrapper

  Rich-content `<dd>` (e.g. multi-line bio, link, badge inline) — the
  consumer can pass HTML-as-string in `definition` and it will be rendered
  via `|raw`. Sanitization is the consumer's responsibility (per kit
  doctrine — see [01-overview.md §I-3] : the kit does not own content).
-#}

{%- set items     = items     | default([]) -%}
{%- set layout    = layout    | default('stacked') -%}
{%- set className = className | default('') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['cremona-description-list'] -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

<dl
  class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}"
  data-layout="{{ layout }}"
>
  {%- for item in items -%}
    <dt class="cremona-description-list__term">{{ item.term }}</dt>
    <dd class="cremona-description-list__definition">{{ item.definition | raw }}</dd>
  {%- endfor -%}
</dl>
